The yeast, Sigma UPS 1, and five spiked levels were each analyzed three times by RPLC, and NCI-20 samples were present as QC mixtures. The Sigma UPS 1 proteins were not detected at the lowest concentration, but each of the other concentrations generated UPS 1 detections, increasing with concentration. This Study reflects the final SOP v2.2 specification for LTQ and Orbitrap instruments.

column12: TRANCHE KEY: bPIBUscVPfkwacbe/87BIjAsGSAZWKH85BzW441WqsyUSwK/NqtfuI/DuXwfjA6gDoM+7qtkbAA72Q2sQmvykcq34s4AAAAAAAAFBA== Data file: B06-9330_O1H2_c. Shotgun proteomics on the osteocytic cell line MLO-Y4, to identify new targets of the anti-osteoporosis drugs Bisphosphonates. MLO-Y4 cells were treated with the Bisphosphonate Risedronate at the concentration 10-7M for 1h and 48h. At the end of the treatment protein extracts were prepared and analysed. The proteome at the basal, untreated condition was used as a reference to whom the proteome from stimulated cells was compared to.

column1: Shotgun proteomics on the osteocytic cell line MLO-Y4
column11: Nicoletta Bivi, Paola Picotti, Lukas N. Mueller, Milena Romanello, Luigi Moro, Franco Quadrifoglio and Gianluca Tell
column12: TRANCHE KEY: bPIBUscVPfkwacbe/87BIjAsGSAZWKH85BzW441WqsyUSwK/NqtfuI/DuXwfjA6gDoM+7qtkbAA72Q2sQmvykcq34s4AAAAAAAAFBA== Data file: OGE07. Shotgun proteomics on the osteocytic cell line MLO-Y4, to identify new targets of the anti-osteoporosis drugs Bisphosphonates. MLO-Y4 cells were treated with the Bisphosphonate Risedronate at the concentration 10-7M for 1h and 48h. At the end of the treatment protein extracts were prepared and analysed. The proteome at the basal, untreated condition was used as a reference to whom the proteome from stimulated cells was compared to.

column1: Shotgun proteomics on the osteocytic cell line MLO-Y4
column11: Nicoletta Bivi, Paola Picotti, Lukas N. Mueller, Milena Romanello, Luigi Moro, Franco Quadrifoglio and Gianluca Tell
column12: TRANCHE KEY: bPIBUscVPfkwacbe/87BIjAsGSAZWKH85BzW441WqsyUSwK/NqtfuI/DuXwfjA6gDoM+7qtkbAA72Q2sQmvykcq34s4AAAAAAAAFBA== Data file: B06-9336_O48H2_c. Shotgun proteomics on the osteocytic cell line MLO-Y4, to identify new targets of the anti-osteoporosis drugs Bisphosphonates. MLO-Y4 cells were treated with the Bisphosphonate Risedronate at the concentration 10-7M for 1h and 48h. At the end of the treatment protein extracts were prepared and analysed. The proteome at the basal, untreated condition was used as a reference to whom the proteome from stimulated cells was compared to.

Proteins were reduced and alkylated using iodoacetamide.  Peptides were produced through trypsin digestion, and the 90-minute RPLC separations (including a one hour shallow gradient) were conducted on an LTQ-XL at the Ayers Institute.  Five centroided tandem mass spectra were collected following each MS scan. column1: Identification of Phosphorylation Sites within the Signaling Adaptor APPL1 by Mass Spectrometry.
column12: TRANCHE KEY: ZEb8WJQd75/i4/POlusCyfWI7czMK+UT3kcIGy8P6caR3iYgUJdGR958BvUpwYS8v6Q56Pe1eiGKjK5H2Y8L/YG/A3kAAAAAAAAEDg== Gant-Branum, RL; Broussard, JA; Mahsut, A; Webb, DJ; McLean, JA.  J. Proteome Res.  2009, submitted. Human embryonic kidney (HEK) cells were transfected with FLAG-GFP-APPL1. After 36 h, cells were then incubated with 1 mM peroxovanadate and 50 nM calyculin A for 30 minutes and extracted. The lysates were precleared twice with mouse IgG-agarose and immunoprecipitated with FLAG-agarose (Sigma, St. Louis, MO) for 2 h at 4 degrees C. Samples were washed and FLAG tagged APPL1 was eluted by incubation of the beads with 0.2 mg/ml FLAG peptide in 25 mM Tris for 30 min at 4 degrees C. For MS analyses, APPL1 was separated into three equal aliquots and proteolytically digested by trypsin, chymotrypsin, and Glu C proteases, respectively. Proteolysis was quenched by adding 1 ul of neat formic acid. Subsequently, the digest was lyophilized and then reconstituted in 25 ul 0.1% formic acid. LTQ chymotrypsin sample.

column12: TRANCHE KEY: bPIBUscVPfkwacbe/87BIjAsGSAZWKH85BzW441WqsyUSwK/NqtfuI/DuXwfjA6gDoM+7qtkbAA72Q2sQmvykcq34s4AAAAAAAAFBA== Data file: B06-9324_OBS2_c. Shotgun proteomics on the osteocytic cell line MLO-Y4, to identify new targets of the anti-osteoporosis drugs Bisphosphonates. MLO-Y4 cells were treated with the Bisphosphonate Risedronate at the concentration 10-7M for 1h and 48h. At the end of the treatment protein extracts were prepared and analysed. The proteome at the basal, untreated condition was used as a reference to whom the proteome from stimulated cells was compared to.

column1: Data_12 - Pseudomonas aeruginosa - Orbitrap - strain PA14, cell lysate
column12: Data obtained from the [[http://www.marcottelab.org/MSdata/Data_12/ authors website]]. Data file: 20090116_SMPA14_3.RAW. From the website: {{i}}Bacterial strains and growth. Pseudomonas aeruginosa UCBPP-PA14 was grown in Synthetic Cystic Fibrosis sputum medium (SCFM), which mimics the nutritional environment of the cystic fibrosis lung and has been previously described (Palmer, 2007). Bacterial growth in liquid media was monitored by measuring the optical density at 600 nm (OD600) during growth at 37with shaking at 250 rpm,m and cells were harvested at an OD600 of 0.4 to 0.5. We performed two biological replications for each experiment. Proteomics experiments. We harvested P. aeruginosa UCBPP-PA14 under the same conditions as described above. After cell lysis with a French press, we spun down cell debris twice (10,000 rpm, 20 min, 4, then removed the supernatant (soluble lysates).{{/i}}

column12: TRANCHE KEY: c9wCnilmFqcPodCpUcaaprfu8865M5jrvHW6YrWwksRKj95BvjNcfltPn9zD6D7QLyoP8E+hieq+ygIscRcaBrmFSFoAAAAAAAAjdw== The Unbiased Discovery Working Group evaluated the sensitivity of spiked protein detection by evaluating samples of yeast with Sigma UPS 1 spiked at five levels. The yeast, Sigma UPS 1, and five spiked levels were each analyzed three times by RPLC, and NCI-20 samples were present as QC mixtures. The Sigma UPS 1 proteins were not detected at the lowest concentration, but each of the other concentrations generated UPS 1 detections, increasing with concentration. This Study reflects the final SOP v2.2 specification for LTQ and Orbitrap instruments.

Shotgun proteomics on the osteocytic cell line MLO-Y4, to identify new targets of the anti-osteoporosis drugs Bisphosphonates. MLO-Y4 cells were treated with the Bisphosphonate Risedronate at the concentration 10-7M for 1h and 48h. At the end of the treatment protein extracts were prepared and analysed. The proteome at the basal, untreated condition was used as a reference to whom the proteome from stimulated cells was compared to.

column12: Data obtained from the [[http://www.marcottelab.org/MSdata/Data_12/ authors website]]. Data file: 20090115_SMPA14_3.RAW. From the website: {{i}}Bacterial strains and growth. Pseudomonas aeruginosa UCBPP-PA14 was grown in Synthetic Cystic Fibrosis sputum medium (SCFM), which mimics the nutritional environment of the cystic fibrosis lung and has been previously described (Palmer, 2007). Bacterial growth in liquid media was monitored by measuring the optical density at 600 nm (OD600) during growth at 37with shaking at 250 rpm,m and cells were harvested at an OD600 of 0.4 to 0.5. We performed two biological replications for each experiment. Proteomics experiments. We harvested P. aeruginosa UCBPP-PA14 under the same conditions as described above. After cell lysis with a French press, we spun down cell debris twice (10,000 rpm, 20 min, 4, then removed the supernatant (soluble lysates).{{/i}}
